meanings.definition: A printed copy of a document or image.
meanings.sent1: I made several printouts of the picture to share with my friends.
meanings.sent2: The teacher handed out the printouts of the assignment to the students.
meanings.sent3: The cat knocked over the stack of printouts, creating a paper snowstorm.
meanings.sent4: Her laughter echoed through the room like a flurry of colorful printouts.
meanings.sent5: The printouts fluttered in the wind, resembling a flock of paper birds.

meanings.definition: The act of producing a printed copy of a document or image.
meanings.sent1: The printouts were ready just in time for the meeting.
meanings.sent2: She was responsible for the printouts of the presentation.
meanings.sent3: The printer worked tirelessly, churning out printouts one after another.
meanings.sent4: His mind was a factory, constantly producing new printouts of ideas.
meanings.sent5: The printouts emerged from the machine like magic, bringing words to life.
